#Text=Jeff Gordon wins the 2013 Goody 's Headache Relief Shot 500
#Text=Wednesday , October 30 , 2013
#Text=Jeff Gordon in 2012
#Text=Image : jez s .
#Text=Hendrick Motorsports driver Jeff Gordon won the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series 2013 Goody 's Headache Relief 500 on Sunday at Martinsville Speedway in Martinsville , Virginia .
#Text=Gordon started the race in ninth , and eventually won his first race of 2013 and snapping a 32-race winless streak .
#Text=The race , contested over 500 laps , featured a season-high 17 caution flags for 111 laps and involving 21 drivers , and 15 different race leaders .
#Text=The race was primarily dominated by championship contenders Jimmie Johnson and Matt Kenseth , who led 123 and 202 laps , respectively .
#Text=However , Johnson fell behind after a caution on lap 218 , and dropped back further into the field after another caution on lap 229 .
#Text=Kenseth relinquished the lead on lap 237 to Clint Bowyer , and was out of the top ten afterwards .
#Text=Gordon took the lead from Bowyer on lap 282 , which he held for 57 laps .
#Text=Johnson and Kenseth eventually caught up to the top ten , while Gordon lost positions due to a pit stop , but he reached second place with 80 laps to go .
#Text=On lap 479 , Gordon passed Kenseth entering turns one and two , and led for the remainder of the race .
#Text=Kenseth finished second , followed by Clint Bowyer , 2012 champion Brad Keselowski , and Johnson closed out the top five .
#Text=Kevin Harvick , pole-sitter Denny Hamlin , Dale Earnhardt , Jr. , Greg Biffle and last week 's race winner Jamie McMurray rounded out the top ten .
#Text=After winning , Gordon stated :
#Text=" It ’s hard to top what it feels like to win , especially when you ’ve been through what this team has been through .
